Configuring two EC2 Instances in Separate VPCs with A Nginx-Server on one of the instances

1. Set up two Amazon EC2 instances, each in a separate VPC.
2. Install and configure a Nginx server on one of the instances, which should be located within a private subnet of its respective VPC.
3. Configure the second EC2 instance, situated in a private subnet of the other VPC, to establish communication with the Nginx server.


